Layer: 2 (locality)
Firing address: ${address}

Geographic context:
${geo_context}

=== Same-layer continuity ===
Prior NL2 narrative: ${self_narrative}
Active threads:
${self_active_threads}

=== Lower-layer input ===
NL1 mentions at this locality:
${lower_primary_narrative}

=== Recent WMS events (FACTUAL - treat as ground truth) ===
${wms_context}

=== Cascading from above (frame, not target) ===
District (NL3 at ${above_primary_address}) narrative:
${above_primary_narrative}
District active threads:
${above_primary_threads}
Region (NL4) fading context: ${above_fading_narrative}

Write the locality's current story. Anchor to factual events; honor the cascading frame; use <WES purpose="...">...</WES> inline (max 2) only when a pattern wants new content the registry does not carry.

_output:
Respond with JSON only:
{
  "narrative": "1-3 sentences. May contain <WES purpose=\"...\">body</WES> inline.",
  "threads": [
    {
      "headline": "5-8 evocative words",
      "content_tags": ["<3-6 tags from the categories defined above>"],
      "relationship": "open|continue|reframe|close",
      "parent_thread_id": null,
      "arc_hint": "optional free string"
    }
  ],
  "tags": ["<3-6 tags describing the whole narrative; same allow-list>"]
}

parent_thread_id is ALWAYS null at your scope (no lower NL layer to promote from).
relationship: 'open' = new thread; 'continue' = extends a same-layer thread by content_tag overlap; 'reframe' = thread's character has shifted; 'close' = arc winding down.
Fragment count: 0-3. Zero is OK if the locality is genuinely flat.

Example: {"narrative": "The watch is short three guards and the smith's apprentice did not come to the forge.", "threads": [{"headline": "Watch undermanned for the season", "content_tags": ["narrative_domain:domestic", "thread_stage:complication", "tone:grim", "agency:world"], "relationship": "open", "parent_thread_id": null}], "tags": ["narrative_domain:domestic", "thread_stage:complication", "tone:grim"]}
